#HTML: FRONTEND/INPUTS

#index.html:

Take: 3-4 Independent Variables: sliders
Take: 0-1 Dependent Variables (If 3 independent variable selected): sliders (restrict too many variable choices with checkboxes)
Take: 0-1 Projectile Preset (Baseball, Paper Airplane, etc.): dropdown (restrict too many variable choices with radio)
Take: 0-1 Manual Input (If custom preset selected): sliders
Take: output preferences (no energyanalysis,no timestamps): radio/checkboxes

JAVASCRIPT: VARIABLE

variabletransferto.js: Extract Variables, push to main.py

#PYTHON: BACKEND/COMPUTING

Take Variables => convert to:

##aeropreset.py: aero presets => mass,cd,area
##solver.py: 3 Indep + 1 Dep => Inferred Independent Variable
##simulation.py: 4 Indep => 4 Dep
##energyanalysis.py: 8 variables => initial/peak/final energy analysis
energy_matplotlib.py: variable_lists => energy time graph
trajectory_matplotlib.py: variable_lists => distance height graph

JAVASCRIPT: VARIABLE

variabletransferfrom.js: extract results, push to index.html

HTML: FRONTEND/OUTPUTS

#index.html: display results

CSS: FORMATTING/enable + disable buttons based on given presets

edit.css: format website


index logic

select 3-4 indep

- checkbox ivel
  - slider ivel
- checkbox iheight
  - slider iheight
- checkbox iangle
  - slider iangle
- checkbox grav
  - slider grav

select 0-1 dep

- radio distance
  - slider distance
- radio maxheight
  - slider maxheight
- radio time
  - slider time
- radio fvelocity
  - slider fvelocity

block dep choice if 4 indep given

select aero profile:

- radio preset:
  - dropdown: soccerball/baseball/paper plane
- radio custom:
  - slider mass
  - slider cd
  - slider area

additional options:

- radio allow timestamps
- radio allow energy analysis